<!-- 07 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Brands we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Residential refrigerator brands by tier.</h2>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Ultra-premium tier</h3>
    <p><strong>Sub-Zero.</strong> Sub-Zero Group, Madison Wisconsin. The LA premium standard. 700-Series, 600-Series, classic 30/36/42/48-inch built-ins, BI columns, refrigerator drawers. Independent family-owned company since 1945. Service through Sub-Zero authorized network. See <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Wolf residential.</strong> Sub-Zero Group sister brand. Wolf primarily makes ranges and cooktops residential, but Sub-Zero Group offers some Wolf-branded refrigeration on integrated kitchen suites. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/wolf/">Wolf refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Thermador.</strong> BSH Home Appliances (Bosch family in US). Premium American-positioned though German-owned. Common in mid-premium LA remodels. Freedom Collection columns popular. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/thermador/">Thermador refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Viking.</strong> Middleby-owned. Premium American manufacturer. Less common than Sub-Zero in LA but distinctive. Different parts catalog from Sub-Zero entirely. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/viking/">Viking refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Miele.</strong> German premium, family-owned Miele Group since 1899. MasterCool series in built-in installations. Different German parts logistics.</p>
    <p><strong>GE Monogram.</strong> Haier-owned since 2016. Premium GE line including built-in refrigeration.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Mid-premium tier</h3>
    <p><strong>KitchenAid.</strong> Whirlpool family. Most popular mid-premium brand in LA. KRFC, KRFF, KBSD, KRSC series. See <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-refrigerator-repair/">KitchenAid refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>GE Profile / Café.</strong> Haier-owned since 2016. Profile is mid-premium, Café is chef-positioned premium. PFE, PWE, CWE, CGE series. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/ge-profile/">GE Profile refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>LG.</strong> Korean (LG Electronics). Dominant in mid-tier. LR series French door, LRMVS InstaView models. Linear compressor technology with known issue patterns we recognize. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/lg/">LG refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Samsung.</strong> Korean (Samsung Electronics). RF series French door, RS side-by-side, Family Hub touchscreen models. Documented design issues with ice makers (multiple class actions). We know how to address. See <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/brands/samsung/">Samsung refrigerator repair</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Bosch.</strong> BSH Home Appliances. German premium-positioned (parent BSH = Bosch + Siemens combined). Common in mid-premium installations.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Mid-tier</h3>
    <p><strong>Whirlpool</strong> (flagship Whirlpool Corp brand, WRF, WRX series), <strong>Maytag</strong> (Whirlpool subsidiary, MFI, MFD series), <strong>Frigidaire</strong> (Electrolux brand, FFTR, FRSS series), <strong>JennAir</strong> (Whirlpool subsidiary, premium-positioned within Whirlpool family), <strong>Kenmore</strong> (historically Sears-branded Whirlpool / LG / Frigidaire OEM rebadge depending on series, servicing depends on actual OEM).</p>
  </div>
</section>

